WHO   — The SIR Model — S → I → R · the epidemic curve
WHAT  — The shape of an epidemic: the susceptible fall ill, the infected recover or are removed, and the curve rises and falls.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because disease moves through a population by contact, and compartments make the movement predictable.
HOW   — By flows dS/dt=−βSI, dI/dt=βSI−γI, dR/dt=γI — transmission against recovery.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the curve everyone learned to flatten: susceptible, infected, removed. Predict me early and you save the most lives.

